Quote: The New Zealand equivalent [to go bung `<i>break down</i>'], puckeroo<i> or</i> be puckerooed <i>sound like an English word used by the maoris and returned with some damage to the voicing of the consonants; but is is actually from the </i> Maori <i>pakaru</i> `break'.
